  ;; ── Design notes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  (text "POWER DESIGN NOTES:\n\n1) USB 5V → F1(500mA polyfuse) → BQ24075 VCC\n   ESD on D+/D- via D2 (PRTR5V0U2X)\n\n2) BQ24075:\n   - ISET: R10=2kΩ → ~445mA charge current\n   - SYS output feeds both LDOs\n   - VBAT to single-cell Li-Ion via D1(SS14) reverse protection\n   - STATUS pin → GPIO for charge indicator (optional)\n\n3) U6 TLV75533 (500mA) → 3V3_MAIN\n   Powers: ESP32-WROVER-E, TFT, encoder logic, LEDs, USB-UART\n   Bypass: 10uF + 100nF at input, 10uF + 100nF at output\n\n4) U7 LP2985-33 (150mA) → 3V3_ANALOG\n   Powers: SI4732 VDD/VA, ES7243E AVDD\n   Ultra-low noise (<30uVrms) critical for ADC audio quality\n   Bypass: 10uF + 100nF at input, 10uF + 100nF at output\n   Route analog ground AGND single-point to digital GND at LDO\n\n5) Decoupling rule:\n   100nF (0402) + 4.7-10uF (0603/0805) at every IC power pin\n   Place 100nF within 0.5mm of VDD pin"
    (at 155 130)
    (effects (font (size 1.8 1.8)) (justify left))
  )
)
